<p>down in tons &amp; would soon fill the waterway up, they have big dredgers constantly at work in the Canal &amp; they are nearly all French<br/>On the 13th of March there was a great stir in the camp for the military police made a raid on the mobs of gamblers who used to play at night time, outside the Battalion area, they used to have scores of candles burning, so as they could see the principal games were banker crown &amp; anchor &amp; two up<br/>This night the military police rode into the mob with their horses &amp; before the chaps knew what was up half of them were down, talk about an uproar sticks stones</p>
